- Each team can have up to 6 people (you can assemble your own team or find like-minded people in the registration file);
- Teams will have 48 hours (from March 31, 16:00 (GMT) to April 2, 16:00 (GMT)) to create a working prototype of a web game on a given topic;
- The finished games will be shared with the whole company, and producers and top managers will evaluate the prototypes and share their comments.

We'll provide food delivery to all participants on both days of the hackathon. On top of that, all teams will get a unique hackathoner's kit.
[Sign up in the document](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1TnLGuVB25Hlaw2JFDEarfi7aQa3w5reN3fx1uYHC3Rw/edit?usp=sharing) before March 28. And don't forget to take [this survey](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScR9D12fa8VdFVEVAzWAC4U-CR9XP8f0DwfKgfyAdhpeeBD4Q/viewform?usp=sf_link) to get your kit and hot meals.

